        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:03PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Snow Lake Shores, or 14 miles west of Ripley, moving northeast at 45
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canaan, Chalybeate, Snow Lake Shores, Murry, Brody, Pocahontas,
Spring Hill, Collinstown, New Canaan, Blue Mountain, Whitten Town,
Hamilton, Middleton, Bethel, Falkner, Tiplersville, Ashland, Winborn,
Crumtown, and Gravestown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northeastern
and northwestern Mississippi...and west Tennessee.</instruction>
